om the white minority, which still owned most of the best farmland 20 years after independence in 1980, to the black majority.\nAround 4,000 white-owned farms were confiscated without compensation, some with deadly violence. (Photo by Zinyange Auntony / AFP) (Photo by ZINYANGE AUNTONY/AFP via Getty Images)          ","dateCreated":"May 08, 2025","is360":false,"isAiEditable":false,"isFilm":false,"isOffline":false,"isExclusiveContent":false,"isEmbeddable":true,"seoTitle":"ZIMBABWE-POLITICS-AGRICULTURE","seoCaption":"Farm workers milk dairy cows in the parlour at Sherwood Park Estates in Kwekwe, Midlands Province, Zimbabwe, on May 8, 2025. Zimbabwean farmers Daniel Burger and Miriam Mupambawashe are neighbours and partners in efforts to rebuild Zimbabwe's once-flourishing agriculture sector cut down by a ruinous land reform drive in the 2000s. The programme was to distribute land from the white minority, which still owned most of the best farmland 20 years after independence in 1980, to the black majority. Around 4,000 white-owned farms were confiscated without compensation, some with deadly violence.","orientation":"Horizontal","usageInfo":"available for |editorial uses|. |learn more|","uploadDate":"2025-05-29T01:01:08.777Z","videoTemplateApp":null,"videoTemplateAppVersion":null,"videoTemplateDimensions":null},{"altText":"milking machine in dairy farm - dairy farmers africa stock pictures, royalty-free photos \u0026 images","fileType":null,"id":"183742592","assetId":"183742592","agreement":null,"agreements":[],"agreementDetails":[],"assetType":"image","family":"creative","editorialOnly":false,"licenseType":"RF","quality":"Common","clipLength":null,"cirActionCount":null,"filmDefinition":null,"seoDuration":null,"filmPreviewUrl":null,"istockCollection":null,"editorialProducts":null,"eventName":null,"eventId":null,"eventDate":null,"eventUrlSlug":null,"thumbUrl":"https://media.gettyimages.com/id/183742592/photo/milking-machine-in-dairy-farm.jpg?s=612x612\u0026w=0\u0026k=20